               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the ruling king, patriarch and metropolitan; names of the donors in supplication formulas; incipits of the texts; directives for the ministers; abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
The text in fol. 3r is written alternately in red and black lines. In fols. 112r-114r, portions of text are rubricated more frequently than in the rest of the text.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The scribe did not strictly follow the ruling lines.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="133ra"/>Fol. 133ra: ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ የሀሉ፡ ምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሁ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ፲ወ፪ተፈጸመ፡ አመ፡ ፪፡ ለኅዳር፨ ለዓ፨ ዓለ፨ አ፨<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 133ra: May his prayer and grace be with the scribe Kidanä Maryam. (The book of) the 12 anaphoras has been completed on 2 Ḫǝdar. For eternity, amen.</foreign>
                        <note>Several letters were added in crude handwriting above the bottom line of the colophon, the letters are no longer legible.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
